## Iteration 3 Summary

**What was run**: commit 011feae (Adam wd=0 with timing/weight-norm diagnostics), killed at step 20k due to CPU slowdown.

**Key diagnostic findings**:
| Step | w_norm | step_ms | val_acc |
|------|--------|---------|---------|
| 5k   | 134    | 72.3    | 2.1%    |
| 10k  | 155    | 73.3    | 2.2%    |
| 15k  | 278    | 73.6    | 2.6%    |
| 20k  | 359    | 105.3   | 3.9%    |

**Root cause confirmed**: Weight norm grows exponentially → denormalized floats in gradients → 10x CPU slowdown.

**Fix implemented** (commit 42753ca): `torch.set_flush_denormal(True)` — flushes denormals to zero on CPU. Does not change optimization dynamics. Next iteration should be able to run the full 100k steps.

